director.bdy:
Enzo Barboni ( July 10, 1922 – March 23 2002), sometimes credited by his peudonym, E.B. Clucher, was an
Italian
film director, cinematographer and screenwriter. Born in
Rome
, he is mostly notable for his slapstick comedies starring
Terence Hill
and
Bud Spencer
. Films he has directed include
They Call Me Trinity ,
Trinity Is STILL My Name! , and
They Call Me Renegade
.
